^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 232 - February 19, 2001 ^*N }
^-
This week's deal was played by ^*BBarry Rigal^*N, originally from London and now living in New York City. Barry was playing with ^*BGertrude Plosky^*N at ^*BHonors Duplicate Bridge Club^*N in New York when this week's deal was played.

Barry is one of the best and most prolific bridge authors in the world today. His articles frequently appear in several major bridge magazines and he has authored or co-authored many excellent bridge books. Barry is also one of the best vugraph commentators there is. If you have ever sat in the vugraph theatre at a North American or World Championship, chances are pretty good that Barry was one of the people at the microphone. Barry's quick and accurate analysis, his familiarity with a wide variety of bidding methods, and his witty comments all contribute toward making vugraph more enjoyable and educational for those in the audience.

Barry is also a very strong player. His work frequently prevents him from playing in major events, but when he gets a chance to play in such events, he is often in contention. Barry won his first North American Championship last summer when he was part of the team that won the ^*BMasters Mixed Teams^*N at the ACBL Summer NABC in Anaheim, California.

