4-3 fits (also known as Moysian fits after ^*BSonny Moyse^*N, a former Editor of ^*BThe Bridge World^*N magazine) provide some of the most interesting and challenging declarer play problems. In this week's deal Barry found himself in a 4-3 fit and proceeded to make his contract, despite the fact that trumps broke 5-1. Barry did receive a little help from the defense, but the sequence of plays required to defeat the contract was not easy to find. See if you can spot how the defense could have prevailed as you read through this week's deal.
